column14: Brain with moderately severe signs of aging (ABC criteria: A3 B2 C2). Insufficient for Alzheimer's disease. Additionally slight cerebral amyloid angiopathy type 1. Also slight age-related tauopathy of astroglia at the temporal pole, possibly caused by trauma. Infarctions were not found.

Brain with slight signs of aging (ABC criteria A1 B1 C0, that means Thal phase 2 out of 5 for plaques, Braak stage 2 out of 6 for tangles; also cerebral amyloid angiopathy type 2, stage 1 out of 3 according to Thal). Including slight alpha-synucleinopathy in the substantia nigra and brain stem, fitting the incidental Parkinson's disease (Braak stage 3 of 6 for alpha-synucleinopathy). No glial tauopathy.

Brain with signs of aging (ABC criteria: A3 B1 C0; (Thal phase 4 of 5 for amyloid beta and Braak stage 2 of 6 for tau; no neuritic plaques in the cortex) with Lewy inclusions in the brain stem [Braak stage 2 of 6 for alpha-synuclein]). Moreover, slight ARTAG and slight CAA type 2 stage 1
Brain without abnormalities. ABC criteria: A1 B0 C0. No ARTAG. CAA type 2, stage 1 according to Thal.

Alzheimer's disease, severe form, with positive family history (brother). Thal phase 5 out of 5 for amyloid beta; Braak stage 5 of 6 for Tau; ABC criteria A3 B3 C3. Additional findings: ARTAG; CAA type 1, stage 1 according to Thal; alpha-synucleinopathy, amygdala-only type. Additionally, an infarction in the right occipital lobe.

Brain with beginning Alzheimer's disease. ABC criteria (according to Montine et al. 2012): A3 B2 C2. No infarctions. Signs of terminal hypoxia. Furthermore, slight cerebral amyloid angiopathy type 1 stage 1 out of 3 according to Thal. Thal phase for amyloid beta. 3 of 5; Braak stage for tau 4 of 6.

Alzheimer's disease, advanced form, especially the parietal cortex is severely affected. The family history is unknown. Thal phase 5 of 5 for amyloid beta, Braak stage 5 of 6 for Tau. Therefore ABC criteria A3 B3 C3. Additionally, severe TDP pathology is found (in the hippocampus and amygdala). Moreover, slight cerebral amyloid angiopathy stage 1 of 3. Very slight alpha-synucleinopathy in the amygdala. No glial tauopathy.
